page.title: 14INTERVIEW:NEWNHAM RESIDENT
page.content: The woman interviewed lived in a semi-detached house.Before that she had lived in Scotland and Canada,both for 15 years.Her husband is a{farm {foreman:}he organises the labour.She is a housewife.They have a Land Rover vehicle but no saloon car. For nights out she and her husband visit friends.They also enjoy musical concerts and plays.At home they have a personal computer,TV and stereo.Her hobby is reading novels.Her favourite TV programme is {Question Time }where politicians face questions from a live studio audience.Her last holiday was in{Canada.} The biggest recent event,she thought, was the royal wedding of{Charles and {Di}in 1981.The biggest change in her own life was going abroad to boarding school when she was young.
